A CHILD went missing during a shoot-out between cops and thugs. This after cops foiled the thugs’ robbery plans in Sandton earlier today. According to police spokeswoman Brigadier Mathapelo Peters, 14 suspects were found with four unlicensed firearms. She said there were five other incidents related to the one at the house. Peters said preliminary investigations were ongoing, but they had bust five other suspects and seized six more firearms. A woman who lives in the area said she heard gunshots at about 8am. “Then I got a call from my niece saying she needs help because she heard gunshots and there were people in the house.” She said she tried to get hold of her sister, who told them a child was missing. Anyone with information about the infant can report at the nearest police station or call Crime Stop on 0860 10111. 